There are regional differences to R

London is said to have the lowest value in England at 0.4 & the north-east the highest

But some experts calculate R as being higher than this

They give a value of 0.8 in Wales, 0.9 in Scotland & 1 in Northern Ireland

https://t.co/3sthIyATFn https://t.co/0cpHIEGV9p

The data used means the R figure generally gives an estimate of where it stood 2 to 3 weeks ago

After creeping up, the latest UK figure is between 0.7 and 1.0

Before lockdown measures were introduced, R was above 3

https://t.co/3sthIyATFn https://t.co/o0O9jgTryg

If the reproduction number is higher than 1, then the number of cases increases exponentially

If below 1, the disease will eventually disappear, as not enough new people are being infected to sustain the outbreak

https://t.co/3sthIyATFn https://t.co/dmnwT9HepY

The R, or reproduction number, is a way of rating the disease‚Äôs ability to spread

It's the number of people that one infected person will pass the virus on to, on average

https://t.co/3sthIyATFn https://t.co/PxWopith9w

There is a simple, but crucial number at the heart of understanding the threat posed by the coronavirus
